==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Autochthon
<hw>Au*toch"thon</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
E. <plw>Authochthons</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, L. <plw>Autochthones</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/, pl. <?/, from the land
itself; <grk>a'yto`s</grk> self + <?/ earth, land.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who is supposed to rise or spring from the ground or the soil
he inhabits; one of the original inhabitants or aborigines; a native; --
commonly in the plural. This title was assumed by the ancient Greeks,
particularly the Athenians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is original to a particular country, or
which had there its origin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autochthonous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Authochthonic</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Autochthonal</ent>⟦br⟧
